      "role": "user",
      "content": "My bad, I'll paste the summary here.\n\nPR #442: Deprecation of AgenticOrchestrator Framework\nDescription: To reduce infra costs and move toward a more scalable stateless architecture, we are phasing out the AgenticOrchestrator module. \nChanges:\n- Remove /core/orchestrator/ logic and state management.\n- Replace all autonomous agent loops with simple, stateless Lambda functions.\n- Deprecate the 'AgentSession' listener.\n- Update all dependency injection to remove 'AutonomousAgent' as a core provider.\n\nBasically, we're moving away from running long-lived autonomous agents and just using standard scripts instead. Let me know if this looks okay from a codebase health perspective.",
